fields.title: Artificial Intelligence
fields.desc: This workshop aimed at teaching Deep learning and Artificial Intelligence in robotics. It gave the students insight on self thinking and decision making algorithms. Since this plays a key role in making AI driven robots it's a very essential skill that students must have if they want to develop their self thinking robots. This was also essential an

fields.title: Arduinobotics
fields.desc: Arduino is the most useful and simple tool for robotics. Easy programming and a wide variety of application gives Arduino the power that very less gadgets possess. The Arduinobotics workshop was aimed on making sure that every student that attended it leaves the Workshop with a complete knowledge of Arduino, from its capabilities to it's limits. It

fields.title: Drone Technology
fields.desc: Most exciting and in trend topic is none other than Drones. The Workshop aimed on teaching Drone Technology and Drone Applications. It also taught IR application and communication between devices. Drones are in itself very intricate and carefully assembled piece of hardware whose function always fascinates the observer. This Workshop was aimed at e

fields.title: IC Engine
fields.desc: The Workshop taught basic functionality of an Internal Combustion Engine. It also talked about the details involved in a 4 Stroke Engine. An IC Engine is a very wide topic where a lot of small parameters affect it's working. These all were discussed during the workshop which contributed to the growth of knowledge which was restricted to classrooms

fields.title: Robo Shoot
fields.desc: Soccer for robots, Score big win bigger. This competition is to show how good and swift robot of yours can be by playing soccer using it and scoring more goals. Numerous colleges participated in the event in which your robot has to score a goal against the opponent's robot. The designing of such robots required intricate and compact design while not compromising on power. It also required innovative thinking and swift running of the robot.

fields.title: Maze Runner
fields.desc: Solve it like Harry did. The game is to make a bot that can solve the maze in a given time. Its a line following bot and you're judged based on time you took. Here the use of IR sensors and related technology is very essential. The students have to keep in mind that the robot is in control and don't go off track. There's good use of coding and a lot of testing is required to get this bot working flawlessly.

fields.title: Terrain Treader
fields.desc: If it can go through the dirt your bot can go through this. Here your bots maneuverability and power is tested. The track is filled with obstacles and hurdles. The winner takes it all. There's a good use of high power and toughness in this not. The participants must make sure there bot functions in rigid and rough conditions without failing. The obstacle track is brutal and doesn't forgive anyone. An agile and tough bot is required for getting gold here.

fields.title: Diabolic Dumper
fields.desc: The competition requires you to design such a mechanism and shift maximum number of balls to deposit zone. Easy?? Here comes the twist in the tale. Your opponent can claim the balls you have collected. You have only two options- get dumped or become the DIABOLIC DUMPER. Not just power it's a game of speed and agility. You may not be the most powerful out of the competitors but if you're the fastest then this is the place for you to be.

fields.title: Aqua Bot
fields.desc: Make a bot that can swim its way through the water. Wired or autonomous it must clear the track underwater. The track has obstacles but the main thing is your bot must be faster than others and should go around the opponents to win the crown. Here the students have to put their brain caps on! as this bot requires a lot of calibration and modifications to make it waterproof. Since it has high chances of failure due to water leakage this bot is really a challenge for all the participants.

fields.title: RoboQuiz 2.O
fields.desc: D2c contest

fields.title: Shell Eco Marathon
fields.desc: Shell Eco-Marathon challenges students to build ultra-energy efficient vehicles. Participants build automotive vehicles to achieve the highest possible fuel efficiency. The competition is huge and therefore, the Shell Eco Marathon is divided into three zones:Asia, Europe and America. We participated in Shell Eco Marathon in 2018, which was held in Singapore. While a normal vehicle gets an average of around 60 km per liter of fuel, our innovative design had an average of 1200 km’s from one liter of Petrol. We secured 3rd Position in India And 17th Position in Asia.

fields.title: ROBOCON
fields.desc: Robocon (short for Robotic Contest) is organized by Asia-Pacific Broadcasting Union (ABU) A Collection of over 20 countries of Asia Pacific Region. In 2018, the competition was held in Vietnam where each country presents a team. Therefore, A Competition to select the best team from India was held in march 2018 at MIT Pune. A team of 40 members from all years participated in this National Level Competition.

fields.title: Wissenaire'19
fields.desc: Wissenaire is organised in IIT BHUBANESWAR it's the one of the biggest techno-management fest across the country. We Acquired the First Prize in BOX MAZE’19 event where we made a bot which moved along walls avoiding to hit it. The group consisted of experienced and hardworking members Consisting of Sri Sai Suhas K, Ayushi Chaudhary, Swapnil Sahu, Mahendra Gabel and Mayank dixit. Maze Solver - Best Mechanical Design Trekkon , Kick off - Best Electrical Design

fields.title: Sensorous
fields.desc: We acquired the 3rd Position in sensuous event wherein we had to make a “Semi-Autonomous Bot” that will follow a track of curves, degrees and crossovers. The bot had to traverse through sharp turns and unexpected changes. In all this the experienced team of ROBOTiX CLUB performed flawlessly and secured 3rd in the event.

fields.title: Wissenaire'16
fields.desc: In the Trekkon event of Wissenaire, the team won the First Prize. They made a bot which could traverse in a rugged terrain and could pick and put desired objects in right place. The team was guided by the able guidance of Ankit Pawar. The team performed effortlessly during the event making this one of the most happening events in Wissenaire.

fields.title: Technex’16
fields.desc: We acquired 2nd Position in the event. The event was organized by IIT BHU wherein we made a bot to traverse though a grid picking objects at different places. The competition was fierce as the bot has to compete against international level Robots with teams coming from various countries.

fields.title: Cognizance’15
fields.desc: We gained 1st Position in the event AHEC. This was organised by IIT Roorkee wherein we made a bot to gain maximum projectile range using water bottle jet. The bot had to face real life problems to make the most out of the limited resources.

fields.title: Cognizance’15
fields.desc: In the Posiedon event Of IIT Roorkee, the Team won the First Prize. Where the bot had to compete in water maze arena using a fast swimmer bot avoiding all the obstacles. The Team was lead by Ankit Pawar. He guided the fellow teammates towards victory.

fields.title: Spazor
fields.desc: We acquired Third Prize in Spazor. Where they had to make an ‘Autonomous Line Follower Bot’ which follows a path made of white lines. The path was haphazard containing 90° turns, bends etc. The Team was guided and leaded by the visionary Pankaj Yadav.

fields.head: HAWK EYE
fields.title: Hawk-Eye “The nightmare to every Umpire and the dream of Every commentator”
fields.desc: The LBW decisions have been the most controversial ever. A review system known as DRS was introduced in cricket to solve this controversy and to lift pressure from umpires. The Hawk-Eye Technology was earlier used for Brain surgeries and Missile Tracking.  It uses six specially placed cameras to track the the path of ball, from when it was released from bowler’s hand till it's dead

fields.head: DRS
fields.title: The Science behind DRS (Decision Review System)
fields.desc: In Snickometer, the stump mic picks up the live sound, filters it and relays it to an oscilloscope attached to it, which then traces the relevant sound waves. In the meantime, cameras record the visual and replay it in slow motion.If the ball is suspected to have hit the bat, the Ultraedge sound graph is checked for impact - a single, sharp spike on the graph will confirm the ball touching the bat.  Hot Spot is a more accurate solution to detecting edges than the Ultraedge as it is not a sound-based edge detection system.  Two cameras placed on opposite sides of the ground record the visuals and yield infra-red images. The principle behind the Hot Spot technology is that contact between bat and ball creates friction and in turn a localised increase in temperature, which appears as a bright spot in the infra-red image.

fields.head: LED STUMPS
fields.title: A distance of few milimeters can break a million hearts
fields.desc: He fell just a few milimeters short, the bails fell and with that, shattered million dreams. One of the most simple yet innovative idea in cricket. LED Stumps have helped Umpires take critical decisions. Robotix Club present the 3rd  video of its "Cricket Video Series"

fields.title: Obstacle Detecting & Edge Avoiding
fields.desc: Exploring the terrains is a tough task and needs help. Obstacle avoidance is a primary requirement for any autonomous mobile robot  Obstacle avoidance Robot is designed to allow robot to navigate in an unknown environment to avoid collisions. Obstacle avoiding robot senses obstacles in the path, avoid it and resumes its running.
fields.members: Rohan Agrawal, Suratna Singh, Arpita Srivastava,

fields.title: Home Automation
fields.desc: Home Automation is a project that works on IoT with the help of ESP8266 NodeMCU, Blynk app and relay to switch on any AC home appliance. The project also displays the status of different appliances on an LCD screen display. IFTTT to send notifications to your Smartphone such as opening of door or any other suspicious activity.
fields.members: Abhinav Mishra, Ansh Srivastava, Mehul Agrawal, Manya Mishra

fields.title: Amphibious Robot
fields.desc: An Amphibious Robot as the name suggests is a robot that goes on land, on water and in water. Amphibious bot can be operated in various means. It can be operated manually as well as it can be an autonomous robot. An amphibious robot, apart from being very attractive and challenging, has a very broad application and can be useful in complex working environment.
fields.members: Aman Swarnkar, Vivek Nag, Christi S Mathai, Apoorva Banerjee

fields.title: Solar Tracker
fields.desc: The solar panel tracker is designed to follow the sun movement so that maximum light intensity hits on the solar panel, thus increasing the power efficiency. Use of a solar tracker circuit in the field of energy production will increase its efficiency by almost 25%. This system can also be successfully implemented in other solar energy based projects water heaters and steam turbines.
fields.members: Vedant A Ashthikar, M Tejaswini, Shreyas Royzada, Aman Verma

fields.title: LED Cube
fields.desc: The 3D LED Cube is a really cool device that enables you to see in three dimensions, get some depth perception and has 512 LED's or 512 pixels.  It is based on an Arduino Uno which is an Atmel AVR microcontroller on a development board with some standard interfacing pinouts that allow you to quickly assemble prototypes.
fields.members: N Suraj Kumar, Priyadarshi Arun, Yogesh Markandey

fields.title: Motion Sensor
fields.desc: PIRs are basically made of a pyroelectric sensor which can detect levels of infrared radiation. Everything emits some low level radiation. The sensor in a motion detector is actually split in two halves. The reason for that is that we are looking to detect motion and not average IR levels. The two halves are wired up so that they cancel each other out. If one half sees more or less IR radiation than the other, the output will swing high or low.
fields.members: Swapnita Goyal, Gyannendra Gavel, Sahitya Singhania, Sanskriti Chandrakar

fields.title: Air Quality Sensor
fields.desc: The project deals with the detecting of the air pollution gases like CO2 , CO , NO2 , SO2 . Our project deals with the detection of the polluting gases like CO2 and CO since this is made on a small scale.
fields.members: Anukriti Das, Shashank Chandrakar, Ashish Kumar

fields.title: Automatic Medicine Vending Robot
fields.description: Design a miniature robot which carries different medicines inside it and will able to follow the different paths to different beds of patients with the help of image processing or sensors by recognizing the line. Each patient should have a separate rfid card through which the medicines can be dispensed according to individual.
fields.requirements:
The Robot should be connected to the app in which the feed can be given for the medicines of different patients according to their rfid. 
The robot should have different sections for different medicines inside. 
For now, design it for 3 medicines.

fields.title: Non-Invasive Water Flow Meter
fields.description:
Background Increasing depletion of water resources generates the need to measure the water flow and find actual utilization. We need an innovative yet cost-effective solution that avoids plumbing need, conforms to compliance and gives a good user interface for end-users to see and control the usage Specifically, the Product required : a) should measure water flow without having to cut a pipeline. b) support compliance Just like any water flow meter, the product evolved should measure flow at an accuracy conforming to ISO4064 and/or Class B c) Cost: must be around Rs.5000/- - Rs.7000/- for a meter that can be used for 20mm pipeline.
Additional problem statement:
All the sensors should report the data wirelessly.
Make your own app to display the data given by the sensors.

fields.title: Smart Silos
fields.description:
There have always been an increased safety in agricultural storage. Silaos and grains elevators can be dangerous places, with conveyor belts that can catch fire and dust buildup that can be explosive. Using sensors to track hazards is of massive value. So to help them, create a way to connect sensors and help farmers make sense of the data from their silos and grain elevators. Using the platform, manufacturers can establish baseline performance norms and set alert and alarm conditions related to temperature, vibration, humidity and other conditions.
Additional problem statement:
Make the sensors wireless.
Make an app to report the parameters to the farmers. And notify (through an alarm in the phone) in case of a fire hazard.
fields.requirements: Using the platform, manufacturers can establish baseline performance norms and set alert and alarm conditions related to temperature, vibration, humidity and other conditions

fields.title: Autonomous Smart Drone
fields.description: UAV's for Disaster Hardware. When man made or natural disasters like a flood or earthquake, etc. happen, it can be extremely dangerous to send first responders in, even though there is an Alerting System Software for people who badly need help. Drones are useful and are helping in the recovery after the disaster, but most require individual pilots, who fly the unmanned aircraft by remote control. That limits how quickly rescuers can view an entire affected area, and can delay actual aid from reaching victims.
fields.requirements: Autonomous smart drones with integrated image processing APIs that have a longer flight time and can relay real time analysis of images to remote locations will help in early detection and adequate mobilization of resources.

fields.title: Real-Time Water Quality Monitoring
fields.description:
Uttarakhand state is blessed with major water resources including large riverine system with its tributaries. In spite of the plethora of water resources, the people of the state are facing the problem of safe fresh water due to slope factor, management issues, urban conglomeration, deforestation and other environmental factors. It is essential to know the quality of water before its consumption for human and agricultural uses. For Continuous monitoring of the water resources, Design a hardware solution to measure quality parameters of water along with an app to enable monitoring of water quality at various locations. Ensure that it is easy to use and connects to mobile device.

Additional problem statement:
Find a way to connect  water monitoring system to house-hold water filter and if the quality of water quality degrades below a certain point then stop the flow of water from the  filter.

fields.title: Mars Rover
fields.description:
The surface of Mars is very uneven, there are rough terrain, slopes, rocks. So design a servilience robot that can move in that terrain and self stabilize itself using gyros and accelerometers while moving on an uneven terrain to provide live stabilized video feed of its surrounding also integrate a gps module to remotely locate the position of the rover. The robot should be remotely operated and should provide live video feed to the operator.

Additional problem statement:
Make a system to report the air quality of the atmosphere of Mars using air quality sensor.
Also develop some kind of actuating hardware system to insert in the soil and find moisture content in it at different points as the rover moves and also send the coordinates where the moisture is monitored.
